# {{ title }} module

## Introduction

The `{{ name }}` module adds a dedicated feature area to the main Laravel application.

It helps organize related routes, configuration, migrations, views, translations, tests, and service logic in a single place.

Use this module when you want to keep a specific feature isolated and maintainable.

---

## Requirements

Before installing this module, make sure the main application provides:

- A working Laravel application
- A configured application structure
- Database access for running migrations
- Any shared models, services, or helpers required by the module

---

## Installation

Install the module using Composer:

```bash
composer require {{ package }}
```

Run the database migrations:

```bash
php artisan migrate
```

